snippet.textDisplay: Hey Michelle, I work in law enforcement and really enjoy seeing you take on different academies and boot camps. I've got some friendly advice for you regarding your pistol magazine setup on your belt for the future. Try to keep your magazines facing the same direction in the magazine holder on your belt or body armor (whichever applies at the time). At 28:48 your mags are facing different directions. This causes an inconsistency during reloads which will likely cause you to fumble and have a slower reload. I recommend going by the "bullets facing the gun" principle. That direction allows you to reach down, grab a mag, and immediately put it into your gun without having to turn it around during the reload. I'm impressed with your attitude towards training. Thanks for the videos!
